  "rationale": "WoodWave has no logo-wall or feature-grid vocabulary, so the SaaS story is remapped onto the brand's editorial voice. The dark hero is the sole inverse bookend and the only accent carrier: it reuses hero-split-media-copy with the one sanctioned display-title-over-media overlap. A gallery-mosaic band (ghost word + bleed + stagger, using the two real brand photos) sells the 'everything in one place' promise photographically instead of with a feature icon grid. The three value_props render as ONE feature-item run (3-object copy array) in an open, staggered collage on cream \u2014 no boxed cards, honoring no-cards-on-cream. Social proof (stat + quote) maps onto a panel band since the brand lacks a logo wall \u2014 flagged: the logos:true request has no WoodWave equivalent, so it is dropped rather than faked. A centered conversion stack closes with typographic arrow links (no buttons). Every non-hero section is primary/panel with no accent, satisfying the single-accent and bookend fidelity rules."
